# 🩻 Medical Imaging XAI

**Explainable, fairness-aware deep learning for medical image classification.**

Detect **pneumonia**, grade **diabetic retinopathy**, and classify **skin lesions**
from open datasets — with **Grad-CAM** visual explanations and **subgroup fairness** audits.

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10%2B-blue)
![PyTorch](https://img.shields.io/badge/PyTorch-2.x-ee4c2c)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-demo-orange)

</div>

---

> ⚕️ **Educational demonstrator — not a medical device.** Uses openly licensed
> [MedMNIST v2](https://medmnist.com/) data. Never use for clinical decisions.
> See [`docs/data_ethics.md`](docs/data_ethics.md).

## ✨ Highlights

- 🧠 **Three clinical tasks, one pipeline** — pneumonia (chest X-ray), diabetic
  retinopathy (fundus), and skin lesions (dermatoscopy).
- 🔍 **Grad-CAM explainability** — heatmaps show *where* the model is looking.
- ⚖️ **Fairness auditing** — subgroup performance and disparity gaps.
- 📊 **Rigorous evaluation** — accuracy, ROC-AUC, confusion matrix, ROC curves.
- 📦 **Real open data** — downloads automatically via MedMNIST; no manual setup.
- 🖥️ **Clean CLI** — `download`, `train`, `evaluate`, `gradcam`, `fairness`.

## 🗂️ Datasets

| Task | MedMNIST dataset | Classes | Source |
|------|------------------|:-------:|--------|
| Pneumonia detection | `PneumoniaMNIST` | 2 | Pediatric chest X-rays |
| Diabetic retinopathy | `RetinaMNIST` | 5 | Retinal fundus images |
| Skin lesion type | `DermaMNIST` | 7 | HAM10000 dermatoscopy |

All are openly licensed (CC BY 4.0) and downloaded on demand into a local
(git-ignored) cache.

## 🚀 Quick start

```powershell
# 1. Environment
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

# 2. Install (CPU-only PyTorch shown; omit the index-url for GPU builds)
pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# 3. One-command demo: train + evaluate + Grad-CAM + fairness (fast, capped)
python -m med_image_xai.pipeline
```

### Or drive it via the CLI

```powershell
med-image-xai download --dataset pneumonia
med-image-xai train    --dataset pneumonia --epochs 5
med-image-xai evaluate --dataset pneumonia
med-image-xai gradcam  --dataset pneumonia --index 0      # -> reports/gradcam_pneumonia_0.png
med-image-xai fairness --dataset pneumonia
```

Swap `--dataset retina` or `--dataset derma` for the other tasks. Outputs
(checkpoints, curves, Grad-CAM overlays) are written to `models/` and `reports/`.

## 🔬 How it works

```
MedMNIST image
   -> normalize / load (data.py)
   -> SmallCNN classifier (model.py)
   -> evaluation: accuracy, ROC-AUC, confusion matrix (evaluate.py)
   -> Grad-CAM heatmap overlay (gradcam.py)
   -> subgroup fairness audit (fairness.py)
```

## 🧱 Project layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/med_image_xai/data.py` | MedMNIST loaders, transforms, and raw-array access |
| `src/med_image_xai/model.py` | `SmallCNN` with a Grad-CAM-friendly conv block |
| `src/med_image_xai/train.py` | Training loop + checkpointing |
| `src/med_image_xai/evaluate.py` | Metrics, confusion matrix, ROC curves |
| `src/med_image_xai/gradcam.py` | Grad-CAM implementation + overlay rendering |
| `src/med_image_xai/fairness.py` | Subgroup metrics + disparity summary |
| `src/med_image_xai/predict.py` | Load checkpoint, single-image inference + Grad-CAM |
| `src/med_image_xai/cli.py` | Typer command-line interface |
| `src/med_image_xai/pipeline.py` | End-to-end demo runner |
| `docs/` | Ethics statement and model card |

## ⚖️ A note on fairness

MedMNIST ships **no demographic labels**, so the bundled fairness demo uses a
reproducible **placeholder** subgroup attribute (clearly flagged in output). For a
genuine demographic audit, pass real metadata — e.g., Patient Age / Gender from
[NIH ChestX-ray14](https://nihcc.app.box.com/v/ChestXray-NIHCC) — into
`subgroup_metrics`. Details in [`docs/data_ethics.md`](docs/data_ethics.md).

## 🧪 Development

```powershell
pytest -q            # unit tests (no downloads required)
ruff check src tests # lint
```

## 📈 Scaling up

- Use `--size 224` and the full dataset (drop `--limit`) for research-grade accuracy.
- Try ImageNet-pretrained backbones (e.g., ResNet) via transfer learning.
- Plug in full clinical datasets: NIH ChestX-ray14, APTOS 2019 / EyePACS, ISIC Archive.

